:HELP   NAME='SRTCDE'.Sort Code
:XH3.Sort Code
:p.The sort code field is used on list screens and reports.
:p.For list screens, it designates the column of the screen to sort
by. However, changing the sort on a list screen is normally done by
entering a value into one of the position to fields at the top of the
screen. For list screens, the sort code field is on the filter screen,
usually access via F13=Filter.
:p.For reports the sort code is on the report prompt screen, normally
towards the top of the screen. To the right of the field should be the valid
options. It is often labeled Sort Option.
:P.Screen: DCTSEGFZ Field: SRTCDE
Type: DECIMAL(2,0)
Location: (11,23)
:EHELP.
