:HELP   NAME=FNCKEYS.Function Keys
:XH3.Function Keys
:P.This screen has the following function keys
:UL.
:LI.:HP2.F1=Help:EHP2.
F1 displays this help text. If used on a field, it includes the help text
for that field. Otherwise, it shows the help text for the entire screen.
:LI.:HP2.F3=Exit:EHP2.
F3 exits a program. Any changes made on the screen will
not be saved, unless the enter key is pressed first.
:LI.:HP2.F4=Prompt:EHP2.
F4 is used to prompt for a value in a field. If a field is followed by a
question mark (?), it can be prompted. Prompting displays a list of the
possible values for the field and allows the user to select an entry
on the list.
:LI.:HP2.F5=Refresh:EHP2.
F5 refreshes the screen. It will load the screen back to the state is would be
in if it was just entered. This can be useful if a value is changed on
another screen, or to just clear any changes made on the screen.
:LI.:HP2.F12=Cancel:EHP2.
F12 cancels out of the current screen. Any changes made on the screen will
not be saved, unless the enter key is pressed first.
:EUL.
:EHELP.
